1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with single image super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a deep but compact convolutional network for image super-resolution. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for image processing. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a multimedia application. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for image super-resolution.
